Three people died and several others were injured in two separate accidents on KwaZulu-Natal’s roads on Tuesday morning. One person died and 15 others, including school pupils, were injured on Dr Chota Motala Road, in Pietermaritzburg. According to Mi7 National Group Emergency Medical Services, a minibus taxi transporting pupils to schools crashed into pedestrians and other two cars. One of the pedestrians died. More than a dozen people, including pupils, sustained minor to moderate injuries. They were stabilised and treated at the scene. Meanwhile, two people died on the N11 at the Amajuba pass, north of Newcastle, during a crash involving three trucks. KZN Emergency Medical Services spokesperson, Robert Mckenzie said one of the trucks lost control and crashed into road construction vehicles and workers. “Paramedics quickly assessed the scene and found one patient sustained serious injuries and one patients sustained minor injuries. They were treated on the scene before being transported to hospital for further treatment,” said Mckenzie.